column2: sunny slight chop- little blue green algae
hot and sunny- light wind had .6" rain last night
sunny and mild- calm- algae in water- some weed bloom
Saw pair of loons. Winds variable.
Variable wind. Had total of 7 inches of rain this month.
Variable wind. Had 3/4 inches of rain this week. Lake still low.
4 inch chop. Over 4 inches of rain this week.
Light wind. Young ducks are flying now.
Light wind. Lake beginning to bloom. Unable to tqke reading after August 9 due to weather and an accident to my hand and boat trouble. Lake turned in second week of September.
Very windy and choppy today when I did the monitoring which I am sure affected the secchi reading. Partly cloudy skies.
Very clear but also very windy. Lake quite choppy. Definitely affected clarity. Because I work during the week- I can only do this on weekends so I don't have a lot of choice in terms of weather.
cloudy and kind of dark. wind fairly calm.
Partly cloudy- light wind- very few boats out in water.
Cool- very cloudy. Visible algae blooms. Lake calm. Aquatic plants seem to be increased over last year.
Windy but sunny. No clouds. Very few boats.

windy- cloudy- and much cooler than previous days. didn't realize until I got out on the lake that I had left my thermometer plugged in and battery was dead...that's why no temperature readings on this day.
no boats out- party cloudy and a slight breeze. lake very quiet. saw 2 loons.
